.SH NAME
.
ftmulti \- multiple masters font viewer
.
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.
.B ftmulti
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ pt ]
.I font .\|.\|.
.
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.
.B ftmulti
is an interactive viewer for variation fonts (Multiple Masters, GX,
OpenType). Its main purpose is to interactively manipulate variation axes
and scroll through named instances. It can also display static fonts.
.
.TP
.B pt
The point size for the given resolution.
If resolution is 72dpi, this directly gives the ppem value (pixels per EM).
.
.TP
.B font
The font file(s) to display.
.
.PP
This program is part of the FreeType demos package.
.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.
.TP
.BI \-d \ W x H
Set the window width to
.I W
px, the height to
.I H
px (default: 640 x 480).
.
.TP
.BI \-r \ r
Use resolution
.I r
dpi (default: 72 dpi).
.
.TP
.BI \-f \ index
Specify first glyph index to display.
.
.TP
.BI \-e \ encoding
Specify encoding tag (default: no encoding).
Common values:
.B unic
(Unicode),
.B symb
(symbol),
.B ADOB
(Adobe standard),
.B ADBC
(Adobe custom), or a numeric charmap index.
.
.TP
.BI \-a \ axis1 , axis2 , .\|.\|.
Specify the design coordinates for each variation axis at start-up.
.
.TP
.B \-v
Show version.
.
.\" eof
